snippet.textDisplay: Well, to all of you Congressmen and women, here is some food for thought: I understand that, sadly, a little over 10,000 people have died nationwide from COVID-19. But, how about we keep this all in perspective, folks? For instance, let’s look at the numbers with regards to fatalities that resulted from motor vehicle accidents. Globally, the number of annual road traffic deaths reached 1.35 million (WHO, 2018). That’s over 225,000 deaths in two (2) months time. (Interesting fact: Again, globally, traffic accidents caused 50 million injuries! {WHO, 2018}). Now, let’s compare those numbers to the number of deaths worldwide for this “pandemic”. To date, in the past two (2) months 79,506 people worldwide have died from COVID-19. (WHO, 2020) And, the highest percentage of these deaths occurred in people 80 years old and up. (Worldometer, 2020) To put this into even better perspective, eventually COVID-19 will “burn itself out”, and will stop causing such large numbers of death. However, and unfortunately the deaths caused by traffic accidents will continue to cause high numbers of death every single year. So folks, given these numbers, WHERE is the global call to action to prevent, or even just lower, the extremely high number of deaths on all of our roadways and all over the world??! I have seen a boatload of websites that provide ALL kinds of STATS, but no solid list of things that can be done to lower those stats. SO, WHERE IS GRETA THUNBERG??!! HEY GRETA! Now, HERE is something that is actually worthwhile to soundly shame everyone at the United Nations about! So, Greta, what do you think, how would you like to REALLY save some lives?! Just think about this, and let it sink in... Before you reach the end of your life, many more deaths on our world roadways WILL personally impact your life than any climate changes ever will. To quote your own words, Greta: “I THOUGHT THAT NOTHING IS HAPPENING—IT IS MY MORAL DUTY TO DO WHAT I CAN.” And, NOW is that time to do what you can do about preventing roadway deaths– you truly CAN save so many lives RIGHT NOW, in your lifetime...not some unknown time in the future.
